wikipedia_page.main: Fred Channell (5 May 1910 – 1975) was a professional footballer who played for Harwich & Parkeston, Haywards Heath, Peterborough & Fletton United, Northfleet United and Tottenham Hotspur.

response: Once back in the First Division, Felton again lost his place, this time to Fred Channell and at the end of the 1933–34 season he was placed on the transfer list. In his two years at White Hart Lane he played a total of 75 games, scoring once from a penalty, in a 1–1 draw with Arsenal on 11 September 1933.Spurs results – 1933–1934
